#
# Source commit: cd090979b7ea78c75e4de8a4aed04f7e9fa8deea (jackson-databind 2.12.x branch)
#   "backport Fix #3590 and Fix #3582 (#3622)" — released as 2.12.7.1
# Target version: 2.12.4
#
# Bundles fixes for both:
#   - CVE-2022-42004 (#3582): BeanDeserializer._deserializeFromArray() did not
#     check for nested START_ARRAY tokens when DeserializationFeature
#     UNWRAP_SINGLE_VALUE_ARRAYS is enabled, allowing stack exhaustion via
#     deeply nested wrapper arrays.
#   - CVE-2022-42003 (#3590): primitive value deserializers in StdDeserializer
#     had the same gap; refactored to share a new handleNestedArrayForSingle()
#     helper that rejects deep wrapper-array nesting.
#
# Note: release-notes/VERSION-2.x changes from the upstream commit are NOT
# included — those headers reference 2.12.5/2.12.6/2.12.7 entries that do not
# exist in the 2.12.4 release-notes file. Excluding them is doc-only and
# does not affect the security fix.
#
# Note: StdDeserializer.java and DeepArrayWrappingForDeser3590Test.java changes
# are intentionally excluded here — they are already applied by CVE-2022-42003.patch.

